---
/**
 * Editorial "in production" block — replaces the long-form body on work
 * entries whose status is "in-production". Points the reader to the two
 * fully-published case studies as a quality reference.
 */
---
<section class="px-5 sm:px-6 md:px-8 pt-20 md:pt-32 pb-12 md:pb-16">
  <div class="mx-auto text-center max-w-(--container-prose)">
    <div
      class="font-mono uppercase text-label text-text-muted inline-flex items-baseline gap-2.5 mb-9 tracking-mono-x"
    >
      <span aria-hidden="true">↳</span>
      <span>Status</span>
    </div>
    <h2
      class="font-serif font-350 m-0 mb-14 tracking-display-xl text-balance"
      style="font-size: clamp(2.25rem, 5vw, 4.4rem); line-height: 1.05;"
    >
      This chapter is <span class="italic">in production.</span>
    </h2>
    <p
      class="font-sans m-0 mb-7 text-pretty"
      style="font-size: clamp(1.05rem, 1.3vw, 1.2rem); line-height: 1.7;"
    >
      The full editorial — brief, process, deliverables, and recognition — will
      be added to the published archive in a future release.
    </p>
    <p
      class="font-sans m-0 text-pretty"
      style="font-size: clamp(1.05rem, 1.3vw, 1.2rem); line-height: 1.7;"
    >
      However, these two case studies are currently published in full — start with{" "}
      <a href="/work/evgo" class="border-b border-current hover:border-accent transition-colors duration-300 pb-px">EVgo.com Redesign</a>
      {" "}or{" "}
      <a href="/work/peggythepanda" class="border-b border-current hover:border-accent transition-colors duration-300 pb-px">Peggy The Panda Book</a>.
    </p>
    <div class="font-mono text-text-muted mt-24 text-lg" style="letter-spacing: 0.4em;">— — —</div>
  </div>
</section>
